Durban - The South African Weather Services (SAWS) has issued a weather alert for parts of the province. SAWS has warned that severe thunderstorms have been observed over parts of Harry Gwala, Umgungundlovu, and Uthukela District. According to SAWS, there is also a possibility of damaging winds, hail and heavy downpours moving eastwards.     Your early afternoon satellite image (26 November 2018). Isolated thunderstorms over the central and eastern interior becoming scattered later today in eastern parts of Eastern Cape and parts of KZN. pic.twitter.com/aSWXbGbirQ Head Personal Lines Sales & Operations at Old Mutual Insure, Hannes Smith, said October has already seen heavy rain, flash floods and hail throughout the region. "Parts of Johannesburg and Pretoria also experienced severe hailstorms at the start of November and authorities have warned that more extreme weather is on the way for the rest of this month. Damage to homes and vehicles as a result of extreme weather can easily amount to hundreds of thousands of rand for property owners and there is even a risk of injury or death if one is not cognisant of how to stay safe," Smith said. Tips on how to stay safe during a storm Personal safety first:   Preparing for extreme weather:   Home safety during a storm:   On the road:  